      "title": "2008 JBMO Problems/Problem 3",
      "pageid": 17041,
      "revid": 216433,
      "text": {
        "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Problem\">Problem</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=2008_JBMO_Problems/Problem_3&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Problem\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Find all prime numbers <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/3/6/7/3674de20e2b78b5790ea714b9dcaa11af6aa2340.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$p,q,r$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"43\" height=\"11\" />, such that <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/f/c/8/fc86cead8b62efbbcd41aae266b4821b20d5ea88.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\frac{p}{q}-\\frac{4}{r+1}=1$\" style=\"vertical-align: -16px\" width=\"111\" height=\"40\" />\n</p><p><br />\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Solution\">Solution</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=2008_JBMO_Problems/Problem_3&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Solution\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The given equation can be rearranged into the below form:\n</p><p><img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/a/f/d/afdbcf64a467fb24a685a815c27ebbfcf2369cce.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$4q = (p-q)(r+1)$\" style=\"vertical-align: -5px\" width=\"152\" height=\"20\" />\n</p><p><br />\n</p><p><img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/e/6/c/e6c746080333ed21cb84fab30d701c606d271adf.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$Case 1: 4|(p-q)$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"132\" height=\"18\" />\n</p><p>then we have\n</p><p><img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/d/7/8/d784da8b015b200cbb2585b22148f5026d7521b3.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$q = ((p-q)/4)(r+1)$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"172\" height=\"18\" />\n<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/b/5/a/b5af1a93fe0d4abd56a1cfbc3f612a89bd06ca43.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$=&gt; (p-q)/4 = 1$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"138\" height=\"18\" /> and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/6/1/1/6113942e693c45b6e2cd60802c34bba041efea93.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$q = r + 1$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"72\" height=\"15\" />\n<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/c/2/1/c21b9fa3f36bd126bc59db543e640419eb65963e.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$=&gt; r = 2, q = 3$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"125\" height=\"16\" /> and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/2/6/2/2621032ec11af3338061c97a0012423e287331a2.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$p = 7$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"43\" height=\"15\" />\n</p><p><br />\n</p><p><img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/b/7/2/b72dc5b9050e770d262edd7859b10a7d1f430495.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$Case 2: 4|(r+1)$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"132\" height=\"18\" />\n</p><p>then we have\n</p><p><img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/2/3/3/233b738e37d6f2659e78966da439f2c9064e2185.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$q = (p-q)((r+1)/4)$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"172\" height=\"18\" />\n<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/4/1/6/416798265260c744f9fa1fd292299b16a824e7b9.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$=&gt; (p-q) = 1$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"120\" height=\"18\" /> and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/9/1/9/9191d31f6e87b3f34deca7d762897907836c5f03.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$q = (r + 1)/4$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"105\" height=\"18\" />\n<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/e/b/0/eb0fd7276d2e36638c42ad6a6ae53b654ac99b7a.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$=&gt; p = q + 1 =&gt; q = 2, p = 3$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"237\" height=\"16\" /> and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/1/e/7/1e7dee679d0b46b1346dcdebe9ae4f6d2ad69f48.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$r = 7$\" width=\"42\" height=\"12\" />\n</p><p>note that if <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/1/4/4/14419a8118a21db18a38a69eb2824181e6dc9967.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$(r+1)/4 = 1$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"104\" height=\"18\" />, then <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/1/6/0/160f66cf9cd3b7ce3e038eda26b092c9459d9989.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$q = (p-q) =&gt; p = 2q$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"176\" height=\"18\" /> which is a contradiction.\n</p><p><br />\n</p><p><img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/8/b/7/8b75f741365a93407c7faf136030931947623afa.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$Case 3: 2|(p-q)$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"132\" height=\"18\" /> and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/6/e/b/6eb9fb6e5291022b36bda95f1fdae957f0a60c73.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$2|(r+1)$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"66\" height=\"18\" />\n</p><p>then we have\n</p><p><img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/0/f/4/0f4c3346ea473ef3cab7b0250bf617c4dd65e592.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$q = ((p-q)/2)((r+1)/2)$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"204\" height=\"18\" />\n<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/a/a/3/aa39a121c22bc04cbd1fbbd5dcb13972df37d692.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$=&gt; (p-q)/2 = 1$\" style=\"vertical-align: -5px\" width=\"141\" height=\"20\" /> and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/2/b/8/2b85b50375f95dc1a8a5b67fb937637a3e60d3b0.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$q = (r+1)/2$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"104\" height=\"18\" />\n<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/4/a/f/4aff347c6d4a420087be12cd229993f635e56b41.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$=&gt; p = q + 2$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"106\" height=\"15\" /> and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/1/7/c/17cc5e34f9eac31c9f5c2b5a321a19f4497900e3.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$r = 2q - 1$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"81\" height=\"15\" />\nWe have that exactly one of <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/c/5/c/c5c731b7d270af97077f3db176ecdb422c4fb6a8.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$q, q + 1, q + 2$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"104\" height=\"15\" /> is a multiple of <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/7/c/d/7cde695f2e4542fd01f860a89189f47a27143b66.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$3$\" width=\"8\" height=\"12\" />.\n</p><p><br />\n<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/c/7/4/c74808999bd9d66fff5c8eef2040480bdcc1a351.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$q + 1$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"39\" height=\"15\" /> cannot be a multiple of <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/7/c/d/7cde695f2e4542fd01f860a89189f47a27143b66.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$3$\" width=\"8\" height=\"12\" /> since <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/f/a/3/fa3a557a3577548dd05e4f4cb0c81299e3dc3722.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$q + 1 = 3k =&gt; q = 3k - 1$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"204\" height=\"16\" />. Since <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/1/7/c/17cc5e34f9eac31c9f5c2b5a321a19f4497900e3.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$r = 2q - 1$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"81\" height=\"15\" /> is prime, then we have <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/6/1/e/61e0331ec13998b5ad05bbb64465ce60cc2630e1.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$2(3k - 1) - 1 = 3(2k-1)$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"201\" height=\"18\" /> is a prime.\n<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/2/0/6/206164994e5b2db9de5fd5b691f86cd9fe90056c.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$=&gt; k = 1 =&gt; q = 2 =&gt; p = 4$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"238\" height=\"16\" /> contradiction.\n</p><p><br />\nAlso, <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/1/2/b/12b4dc9cb8b0cb0dfe2e35c5a214057168bc8a06.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$q + 2$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"39\" height=\"15\" /> cannot be a multiple of <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/7/c/d/7cde695f2e4542fd01f860a89189f47a27143b66.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$3$\" width=\"8\" height=\"12\" /> since, <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/a/c/1/ac1cd6986679f4f050a6845665968c7a98dc10a1.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$q + 2 = 3k =&gt; p = 3k =&gt; k = 1 =&gt; q = 1$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"338\" height=\"18\" /> contradiction.\n</p><p><br />\nSo, <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/c/1/7/c17b71c9b2170bb1a1561683bb62467d9c86074b.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$q = 3k$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"51\" height=\"16\" />\n<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/5/f/7/5f702a8656d73027bd60e6841a4401c1f2ed9534.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$=&gt; k = 1 =&gt; q = 3, p = 5$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"207\" height=\"16\" /> and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/9/2/7/9275b0ae5f64b056616640d971b52c3da017dd55.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$r = 5$\" width=\"41\" height=\"12\" />\n</p><p>Thus we have the following solutions: <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/a/f/f/affaa791ce1c911635afde8df1c70c2d936616d1.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$(7, 3, 2), (3, 2, 7), (5, 3, 5)$\" style=\"vertical-align: -5px\" width=\"191\" height=\"20\" />\n</p><p><br />\n<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/a/b/8/ab8a050ca0f84a6aef15ead346438c2777533f30.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$Kris17$\" style=\"vertical-align: -1px\" width=\"60\" height=\"14\" />\n</p>\n<h2><span id=\"Solution_2_(similar_to_Solution_1,_credit_to_dskull16)\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Solution_2_.28similar_to_Solution_1.2C_credit_to_dskull16.29\">Solution 2 (similar to Solution 1, credit to dskull16)</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=2008_JBMO_Problems/Problem_3&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Solution 2 (similar to Solution 1, credit to dskull16)\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The equation can be rearranged into this form\n</p><p><img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/f/1/c/f1cdeb992434e3aaf7f2480d48dfca65c31aeea0.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\frac{p(r+1)-4q}{q(r+1)} = 1$\" style=\"vertical-align: -18px\" width=\"143\" height=\"45\" />\n<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/e/f/6/ef6579d8a9ba73c329adda4c9c3e9572c1d8d4ed.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\implies p(r+1)-4q = q(r+1)$\" style=\"vertical-align: -5px\" width=\"237\" height=\"20\" />\n<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/3/5/d/35dcfdc9407ff7b2b49b7cef42c7afe82909caee.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\implies (p-q)(r+1) = 4q$\" style=\"vertical-align: -5px\" width=\"197\" height=\"20\" />\n</p><p>By the nature of primes this means that either q divides (p-q) or (r+1) and if q divides (p-q) then that means that q divides p which is a contradiction since any two primes have a GCD of 1 meaning that q divides <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/b/0/d/b0db46b36f2b47d778e5dd286ef81651a5e9f6be.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$(r+1)$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"52\" height=\"18\" />. We can easily deal with the case where r is 2 but this gives a contradiction since we get that <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/e/1/1/e118483b349bf51c2f1b7a76b29de0470c136fe9.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$p=6$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"43\" height=\"16\" /> where it needs to be prime.\n</p><p><img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/1/d/e/1de312f86c0f4552122d946ac7970e0eb14d6e9f.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$(r+1) = kq, k \\in \\mathbb{N}$\" style=\"vertical-align: -5px\" width=\"152\" height=\"20\" />\n<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/1/b/e/1be638ea2d64ffdf2a1a4f6ab0d924ac860765ff.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\implies (p-q)(kq) = 4q$\" style=\"vertical-align: -5px\" width=\"176\" height=\"20\" />\n<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/8/2/6/8265f65847dade709e1b7aeaa9472fa36abd861c.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\implies (p-q)k = 4$\" style=\"vertical-align: -5px\" width=\"144\" height=\"20\" />\n</p><p>In the case k is 4, we get that p and q have a difference of 1 meaning that <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/d/e/f/defaa1d57702d95eba6167719c468a1b0931e7f8.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$p=3, q=2$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"94\" height=\"17\" /> and therefore <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/b/1/0/b107efbe3140489fd109c12def149ff23bad8e9c.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$r=7$\" style=\"vertical-align: -1px\" width=\"44\" height=\"14\" /> which clearly works.\n</p><p>In the case that k is 2, we get that p and q have a difference of 2 meaning that <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/3/1/b/31b446688f980f289749458617792104cc4f86d4.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$p=5, q=2$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"94\" height=\"17\" /> and therefore <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/3/1/f/31faa8c684ba5811ac60ea1bd0c855d8ef4d8b16.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$r=3$\" width=\"41\" height=\"12\" /> which also works.\n</p><p>In the case that k is 1, we get that p and q have a difference of 4 meaning that <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/3/9/5/39546972157439dc32c5366d9f23a2b2e7961955.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$p=7, q=3$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"94\" height=\"17\" /> and therefore <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/8/c/c/8cc63d5667f0a88fc3d53c6d20c92b5be6dd5595.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$r=5$\" width=\"41\" height=\"12\" /> which works too and is our final solution.\n</p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20240907212244\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.033 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.034 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 412/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 1096/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 0/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 9811/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    0.000      1 -total\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key wiki-wiki_:pcache:idhash:17041-0!canonical 